HEADWORD: Rueful
<hw>Rue"ful</hw> <pr>(r⟦udd⟧"f⟦usdot⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Causing one to rue or lament; woeful; mournful;
sorrowful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressing sorrow.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Rueful</xex>
faces.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two <qex>rueful</qex> figures, with long black cloaks.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rue"ful*ly</wf>, adv. -- <wf>Rue"ful*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
